 An alleged female drug dealer is expected in court on Monday after she was arrested on Sunday in New Brighton, Port Elizabeth. The 31-year-old woman was arrested after police received a tip-off that she was peddling drugs at her home. “At 00:45 members of SAPS Flying Squad received information about drugs being sold at a home in Penxe Street, New Brighton. “On searching the house, a bag of almost a kilogram of dagga, 10 bompies of dagga, 24 mandrax tablets, 185 Tik lollies and almost 4 000 medical vials were found and confiscated,” police spokesperson, Captain Andre Beetge, explained. She faces a charge of dealing in drugs when she appears before the New Brighton Magistrate’s Court. 